b"
<p>This role is very high profile and will suit someone who understands the complex nature of a bank's balance sheet and its drivers, and is also able to provide detailed insights and analysis to senior executives on the strategic direction it should take.
 You will have access to key decision makers so future opportunities are unlimited.</p>
<p>\xc2\xa0</p>
<p>Responsibilities:</p>
<ul>
<li>Assist in the delivery of both the short-term and long-term balance sheet management forecasts and strategies;
</li><li>Provision of detailed, ad hoc financial analysis and analytics to drive strategic Group Treasury level conversations;
</li><li>Obtain and manipulate key information from numerous data sources to ensure a full scope of analysis is provided;
</li><li>Ad hoc reporting and financial analysis as required by senior Treasury and Banking stakeholders and Executives.</li></ul>
<p>\xc2\xa0</p>
<p>Experience:</p>
<ul>
<li>Excellent academics with a strong analytical background; </li><li>Excellent knowledge of the balance sheet drivers of a bank or other large financial institution;
</li><li>Proven background influencing key stakeholders through detailed financial analysis;
</li><li>Excellent technical skills including SQL, SAS, VBA would be highly regarded; </li><li>Strong attention to detail and the ability to communicate complex issues to a non-numerical audience;
</li><li>The ability to work in a dynamic environment.</li></ul>
<p>\xc2\xa0</p>
<p>To be considered, simply apply below or send and updated CV to james.pang@tomexecutive.com, or call James Pang on (02) 8270 0538 for a confidential discussion.</p>
"

