<p>This is an excellent opportunity for a strong business partner with excellent data analysis skills to join a leading international organisation and drive the headcount and workforce planning strategy for short and long-term engagements. You will gain excellent
 business exposure and have the ability to influence and drive outcomes.</p>
<p>\xc2\xa0</p>
<p>Responsibilities:</p>
<ul>
<li>Delivery of the management reporting and business partnering across this key technology department;
</li><li>Delivery of the budgeting, forecasting, and insightful analysis across all headcount across contract and permanent staff;
</li><li>Detailed financial modelling and data manipulation across numerous data sources;
</li><li>Drive the commercial message around headcount structure and requirements for the technology business;
</li><li>Ad hoc project related analysis and reporting.</li></ul>
<p>\xc2\xa0</p>
<p>Experience:</p>
<ul>
<li>Ideally CA/CPA qualified; </li><li>Strong understanding of the workforce planning considerations in a technology environment and the impact of various vendors and contractor relationships;
</li><li>Proven background delivering insights and analysis to senior business stakeholders;
</li><li>Strong data manipulations skills; SQL, SAS; </li><li>The ability to work in a dynamic environment and influence key decision makers.</li></ul>
<p>\xc2\xa0</p>
<p>To be considered, simply apply below or send and updated CV to james.pang@tomexecutive.com, or call James Pang on (02) 8270 0538 for a confidential discussion.</p>
'

