<p>Excellent opportunity is available for a dedicated IT technical support Level 1 to join our busy and energetic team\xc2\xa0in Australia.\xc2\xa0</p>
<p><strong>The main job responsibilities include but not limited to:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Carry out the IT production support and maintenance tasks for the day to day business of KVB;
</li><li>Deploy and maintain IT Desktop/infrastructure projects in an established global IT environment;
</li><li>Support desktop applications and hardware such as printers, faxes, voice recording system, VOIP PBX, Windows/MS Office, data backup and office security;
</li><li>Assist ongoing maintenance and upgrades of the group IT infrastructure (LAN/WAN);
</li><li>Respond to initial requests for support and resolve where possible within skill set and agreed time-frames
</li><li>Provide on-site, telephone and remote support across Sydney and Melbourne offices;
</li><li>Liaise with internal IT support and Vendor to solve IT requests;</li></ul>
<p><strong>Ideal candidates should come with:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Good command of English and Mandarin (Native) is preferred; </li><li>Hands-on experience on IT Desktop, Applications and infrastructure operational support, minimum\xc2\xa02 years of previous working experience, preferably within the Financial/Banking\xc2\xa0sector;
</li><li>Experience on Windows 7/8/10, Active Directory, MS Office 2007-2013, Anti-Virus Software knowledge and back-up knowledge
</li><li>Experience on Cisco/MS Exchange/O365/Desktop Virtualization/McAfee/Backup Exec is preferred;
</li><li>Experienced in complex projects /scenario handling /coordination &amp; planning, as well as vendor management;
</li><li>Excellent communication, interpretation and presentation skills to transform IT technology language/terms to understandable language;\xc2\xa0
</li><li>IT related tertiary\xc2\xa0degree and relevant up-to-date IT qualification(s)/certificate(s);\xc2\xa0
</li><li>Eligible to work in\xc2\xa0<strong>Australia</strong>\xc2\xa0with a valid working Visa.</li></ul>
<p><strong>You will be rewarded with:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>CBD</strong>\xc2\xa0based top class office working environment; </li><li>An amazing and encouraging company culture that focuses on nurturing and developing our people;
</li><li>Excellent personal development opportunity with a fast growing global organization.</li></ul>
<p>If the above sounds exciting to you; please email your application including cover letter and resume to<strong> erin.y@kvbkunlun.com</strong></p>
<p>Interview starts immediately. Only short listed candidates will be contacted.</p>
<p>No agencies please</p>
<p>\xc2\xa0</p>
